<font color="#FF0000">WALKING BY FAITH</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 23 19:13:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Cook,<br><br>
I was in DC a few years ago. Had plenty of money for my vacation. Can't remember too many times that this working man (me) ever had extra loot for some fun.<br><br>
It was early on a Saturday and the particular museum we were to visit hadn't opened yet. We passed a black man who was panhandling.<br><br>
I stood at a refreshment stand for a few minutes and kept looking at the man - who was standing perhaps 50 feet away. He stood upright and looked straight ahead. I told my wife that I would be right back.<br><br>
When I approached the man I asked him where he lived. He said that he was a homeless Vietnam Vet. I have heard my share of imposters, so I asked him where he served. He said the 25th at Tay Ninh. Sounded good to me. I talked to him for a while and found out that he stayed in a shelter not too far away. His biggest concern was that winter was approaching and he didn't have a warm coat. I slipped him a couple of bucks. You know what? After reading your above post, something dawned on me.<br><br>
When I used to attend church people griped terribly about where their tithes and offerings would ultimately wind up. I remember one person in a place of santuary complaining about some of our church money going to the United Negro College Fund. <br><br>
There are those who walk by faith. Some walk by sight. If the man in DC had been a fake, he is the one that would answer for his transgressions. The money I gave him was given in good faith, regardless of who or what he was.<br><br>
You spend way too much time on this website passing judgment. Charles Robb, for instance. You have lost sight of the obvious fact that every avenue of escape was open for him to NOT serve in a combat zone. He was the son-in-law of the Commander In Chief! He served anyway. What is it about him that you resent? He was the subject of media events? So what?<br><br>
His wearing the Vietnam Service Medal is enough to attest to his service. Same as anyone else. I cringe to think of the vengeance you would wreak upon Robb had he taken advantage of his connections and opted not to serve! He would be just another coward wouldn't he?<br><br>
Love and mercy is the only way. In these we do good.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman#greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


